glosses: For tongue, palate or teeth to become numb or tingle because of something sour.
For eyes to rapidly and involuntarily blink due to touching or a bright light.

etymology: From Ottoman Turkish قماشمق (ḳamaşmaḳ, “for the eyes to be dazzled, for the teeth to be set on the edge”), from Proto-Turkic *kamaĺ- (eye or teeth to tingle, to prickle), from Proto-Turkic *kama- (to become blunt, to go numb).
